## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Vite + React + TypeScript project.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package (version ^2.0.1) to project dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependencies

**2. Modified Files**
- `src/App.tsx`: Added Analytics component integration
  - Imported `{ Analytics }` from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the main app component (placed within TooltipProvider for proper context)

### Implementation Details

Following the latest official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:

1. Installed the package using `npm install @vercel/analytics`
2. Imported the Analytics component from the React-specific entry point
3. Placed the component in the root App component where it can track all routes via React Router
4. The Analytics component is positioned at the end of the JSX tree to ensure proper page tracking

### Configuration Notes

The Analytics component is framework-aware and will automatically:
- Track page views across all React Router routes
- Send analytics data to `/_vercel/insights/*` endpoints
- Work seamlessly with the existing BrowserRouter setup

### Testing Performed

✅ Build: Successfully compiled with no errors (`npm run build`)
✅ Linter: No new linting errors introduced (pre-existing warnings remain)
✅ Tests: All tests passing (1/1 test suites passed)

### Next Steps

To enable analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*` routes

The implementation is complete and ready for deployment.
